{"word":"ἐξοιστέος","slug":"ἐξοιστέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐξοιστέος</b></el> <el>(ἐξοιστέος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <el>ἐξοίσω</el> \n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> of <a href='S:ἐκφέρω'><el>ἐκφέρω</el></a>\n<p/><i>to be brought out</i>: <el>ἐξοιστέον</el>, <i>one must bring out</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/>"}]}